  <!-- ═════════════ TABLE ═════════════ -->
  <section class="relative bg-paper py-20 md:py-24">
    <Container width="wide">
      <div class="mb-10 flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--color-text-head)]">
        <span class="block size-2 bg-scooter"></span>
        <span class="font-display text-[14px] tracking-[-0.005em]">18 · Tables</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="am-h2-display mb-12 text-[var(--color-text-head)]">Comparison / data</h2>

      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[6px] border border-line bg-white">
        <table class="w-full text-left">
          <thead class="border-b border-line bg-paper">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-5 py-4 font-display text-[12px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-[var(--color-text-body)]">Entity</th>
              <th class="px-5 py-4 font-display text-[12px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-[var(--color-text-body)]">Tax treatment</th>
              <th class="px-5 py-4 font-display text-[12px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-[var(--color-text-body)]">Owner draw</th>
              <th class="px-5 py-4 font-display text-[12px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-[var(--color-text-body)]">Best for</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {[
              ['LLC',     'Pass-through',   'Member distribution', 'Single-owner ops, real estate'],
              ['S-Corp',  'Pass-through + payroll', 'Salary + distribution', 'Owners with $80K+ profit'],
              ['C-Corp',  '21% federal', 'W-2 + dividend', 'VC-backed startups'],
              ['Sole Prop', 'Schedule C', 'Owner draw', 'Freelancers, side projects'],
            ].map(([entity, tax, draw, fit], i) => (
              <tr class={i % 2 === 0 ? '' : 'bg-paper/40'}>
                <td class="border-t border-line px-5 py-4 font-display text-[14px] font-medium text-[var(--color-text-head)]">{entity}</td>
                <td class="border-t border-line px-5 py-4 font-display text-[14px] text-[var(--color-text-body)]">{tax}</td>
                <td class="border-t border-line px-5 py-4 font-display text-[14px] text-[var(--color-text-body)]">{draw}</td>
                <td class="border-t border-line px-5 py-4 font-display text-[14px] text-[var(--color-text-body)]">{fit}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <!-- ═════════════ LONG-FORM PROSE ═════════════ -->
  <section class="relative bg-white py-20 md:py-24">
    <Container width="wide">
      <div class="mb-10 flex items-center gap-3 text-[var(--color-text-head)]">
        <span class="block size-2 bg-scooter"></span>
        <span class="font-display text-[14px] tracking-[-0.005em]">19 · Long-form prose</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="am-h2-display mb-3 text-[var(--color-text-head)]">.prose-am — for blog &amp; service bodies</h2>
      <p class="mb-12 max-w-[60ch] font-display text-[15px] leading-[1.65] text-[var(--color-text-body)]">
        Wrap migrated WordPress markdown bodies (or any long-form MD) in <code class="rounded-[4px] bg-paper px-1.5 py-0.5">.prose-am</code>. Handles h2/h3 with cyan teal underline, lists with arrow bullets, blockquotes with decorative quote, and tables.
      </p>

      <article class="prose-am rounded-[6px] border border-line bg-white p-8 md:p-12">
        <h2>What S-Corp election actually saves you</h2>
        <p>For owner-operators clearing $80K+ of profit, an S-Corp election can drop your self-employment tax bill by 12-18% — but only if reasonable comp is set correctly and payroll is run from day one.</p>
        <h3>How the math works</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Salary portion is subject to FICA (15.3%)</li>
          <li>Distribution portion skips FICA entirely</li>
          <li>IRS expects "reasonable comp" set by industry benchmarks</li>
        </ul>
        <blockquote>The IRS doesn't publish a magic ratio. It does publish industry comp tables you can defend against.</blockquote>
        <h3>When it doesn't make sense</h3>
        <p>Below ~$50K profit, the added compliance cost (payroll, annual return) usually outweighs the FICA savings.</p>
      </article>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <!-- ═════════════ TOAST / SUCCESS STATES ═════════════ -->
